THE  secured the first interview with the 'Tache Man' who set last night's leaders' debate alive with his barnstorming appearance.
Taxi driver and tribute band frontman Danny McAfee said he wanted to put a smile on people's faces and lighten up the debate.
He also hopes his performance will encourage and inspire others to get out and vote in next month's general election.
The 54-year-old, father of two, told us he still can't quite believe how dramatically his 15 seconds of fame has changed Scotland's political landscape.
